keyValuePair.Value: Are you ready to take on %1s?
It's the game everybody's talking about. There's so much at stake. Do you feel your team's ready to take on your great rivals?
I hope we're up to the job.
We've been inconsistent recently so I'm not sure what will happen. I've prepared the team as best I can and now we'll just have to wait to see if the boys are up to the job.
We'll show what we're capable of.
We've done everything we can to prepare properly. And I trust my players on the big occasion. I'm sure they'll turn in a good performance. I know what they can do.
We've done everything we can to prepare properly. And I trust my players on the big occasion. I'm sure they'll turn in a good performance. I know what they can do.
The win's what matters.
Of course it's a big game because we're facing our rivals. But, from my point of view, what's really important is the result. Qualifying is a big target for us as a club.
Will you be cautious?
On paper, %1s and %2s look pretty well-matched. What can we expect from your team? Will your plan be to take a cautious approach in such a big game?
We know our targets.
We have clear targets as a club and we know that, as a team, we have to live up to those expectations. We'll need to be at our best to secure qualification.
The team's feeling positive.
I think we've run into some good form at just the right time. The boys are feeling confident. We'll go out there today believing we can win and qualify.
We'll play our football, I promise.
%1s teams are expected to play a certain way: aggressive, technical, positive. I see no reason why that's going to change against %2s today. We'll go all-out for the win.
Are your players looking tired?
There's a lot at stake: it's important to qualify. Are you conscious fatigue could be a factor, even against these opponents? How are you managing your squad in that respect?
We know what we're doing.
Managing the players' fitness is a big part of my job. We know who's ready to play and who needs a rest. As always, we adjust our preparations accordingly.
It's all part of the game.
It's a busy time and there's a lot at stake in this game. Handling fatigue, mentally and physically, is part of the challenge. We'll do whatever we need to do to qualify now.
Is tiredness really an issue?
I know my lads would rather play than train! If you're winning games, you don't feel tired. Let's get out there and secure qualification. We can look to rest and recover later, can't we?
Are you feeling good about your chances?
You definitely look the stronger of the two teams. On paper, at least. Have you any doubts about your team qualifying?
This is a step along the way.
It's how the competition works: you play what's in front of you and then that brings on the next, tougher challenge. I'll be very angry if we don't win today.
I'm confident, certainly.
I'm confident, certainly.
There's no doubt %1s will be fired up for this game. But I'm confident the lads will handle that. Our quality really should tell in the end. We'll qualify, I'm sure.
We'll take the game seriously.
They say pride comes before a fall. We have to be professional about the game, even if we're strong favourites. There's a job to do and we need to focus on being at our best.
Can your team qualify?
Looking at the two teams, you'd have to say this looks like a very big challenge for your boys against excellent opponents. Can you surprise everybody and qualify?
We'll struggle, probably.
I'm not going to pretend I think we've much chance. We know all about how good %1s are. It'll take a miracle for us to qualify now.
We'll do what we can.
This is going to be an uphill battle. I can't pretend otherwise. But I know my lads believe in themselves. We won't go down without a fight, that's for sure.
Let's see how the game goes.
We may be big underdogs but anything can happen in a game. Now's not the time for predictions. Let's see where we are afterwards, shall we?
Can you spring a surprise?
Your %1s team goes into the game as real underdogs. Do you believe you can qualify? And how will you set up your team to give yourselves a chance?
Maybe we're better than you think.
Yes, we're up against a good team. But don't underestimate my players. You might be surprised. These boys have more quality than people give them credit for.
We've got nothing to lose.
We know we're expected to lose, but perhaps that will take the pressure off my players. We'll go out and fight for our chance to qualify, I promise. Let's see what happens.
I'm not optimistic!
I'm not optimistic!
I'm not a fool. I know we're up against a good team. I'm not sure how the game will go. We'll do our best and hope that we can keep our pride intact, whatever the result.
